ZH: 我不小心把面包烧焦了。
EN: I accidentally burnt the bread.

ZH: 他们的晚餐被烧焦了。
EN: Their dinner got burnt.

ZH: 厨房里散发着烧焦的味道。
EN: There's a burnt smell coming from the kitchen.

ZH: 妈妈总是把煎鱼烧焦。
EN: Mom always burns the fried fish.

ZH: 烧焦的烤玉米很难吃。
EN: Burnt corn on the cob is not tasty.

ZH: 由于烧焦，厨房里冒出了浓烟。
EN: Smoke billowed from the kitchen due to the burning.

ZH: 煎蛋的时候你要小心，不要让它烧焦。
EN: Be careful when frying eggs, don't let them burn.

ZH: 我的手指被烧焦之后很痛。
EN: My fingers hurt after getting burnt.

ZH: 他试图搭救那些被烧焦的饼干。
EN: He tried to salvage the burnt cookies.

ZH: 烤苹果派烧焦了，看来我得再做一个。
EN: The apple pie got burnt, looks like I have to make another one.

ZH: 烧焦的肉闻起来很难闻。
EN: Burnt meat smells bad.

ZH: 厨房里有一些烧焦的面包。
EN: There are some burnt bread in the kitchen.

ZH: 这个月已经有三次我烧焦晚餐了。
EN: I burnt dinner three times this month already.

ZH: 煤气灶上的一锅汤烧焦了，煤气灶坏了。
EN: The pot of soup on the gas stove burnt and now the stove is broken.

ZH: 大火把所有的家具都烧焦了。
EN: The fire burnt all the furniture.

ZH: 烧焦的米饭并不好吃。
EN: Burnt rice is not tasty.

ZH: 我的手被烧焦了，好疼。
EN: My hand got burnt, it hurts.

ZH: 烧焦的糖果不好吃。
EN: Burnt candy is not tasty.

ZH: 如果烤面包烧焦了，你就不要吃了。
EN: If the toast is burnt, don't eat it.

ZH: 昨晚我的面条煮烧焦了。
EN: Last night I burnt the noodles.
